<div class="need-to-cancel">
  <div class="affect-poster">
    <strong>Request that your Poster cancel.</strong><br>
    <br>
    If your Poster let you know that his listed employee is not
    available anymore, don't cancel for him/her. Instead, send
    the Poster a message asking him/her to cancel to make sure you receive a
    full refund.

    <%= form_tag cancel_hiring_hiring_path(id: @transaction.id), method: :patch, id: "cancellation_reason_form" do |f| %>
      <%= hidden_field_tag "reason", "The poster needs to cancel" %>
      <%= submit_tag 'Send message to Poster', class: 'continue-btn' %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
